cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GR. 

This paper deals with the recognition of weakly simple polygons, which is a fundamental question in computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The algorithm presented in the paper has a time complexity of O(n log n), which suggests that it involves some data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The paper also involves some combinatorial arguments, which makes cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a possible category. The recognition of weakly simple polygons is related to planar graphs, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with geometric algorithms, which makes cs.GR (Computer Graphics) a possible category as well.
